{"id":25806,"date":"2018-01-27T06:11:26","date_gmt":"2018-01-27T02:11:26","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=25806"},"modified":"2025-02-17T13:20:19","modified_gmt":"2025-02-17T09:20:19","slug":"malik-asma-wa-sifat-kayfiyyah","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/01\/27\/malik-asma-wa-sifat-kayfiyyah\/","title":{"rendered":"Malik on Divinity: Attributes of Allah affirmed, modality unknown"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abdullah ibn Nafi\u2019 reported: Imam Malik, may Allah have mercy on him, was asked about the saying of Allah Almighty, &#8220;<strong>The Most Merciful rose above the Throne<\/strong>,&#8221; (20:5). The man said, \u201cHow is His rising?\u201d Malik said, \u201cThe rising is acknowledged, its modality is unknown, and asking about it is an innovation. I see you are a man who intended evil with this question.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Istidhka\u0304r 2\/529<\/p>\n<p>Ibn Abdul Barr said, \u201cThe people of the Sunnah agreed upon affirming the divine attributes as reported in the Book and the Sunnah, interpreting them as reality and not as a metaphor, except that they do not ask &#8216;how&#8217; is the modality of any of that.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-\u2018Ulu\u0304w lil-\u2018Ali\u0304 al-Ghaffa\u0304r 1\/250<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0646\u064e\u0627\u0641\u0650\u0639\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0633\u064f\u0626\u0650\u0644\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0643\u064c\u00a0\u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0642\u064e\u0648\u0652\u0644\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0632\u0651\u064e \u0648\u064e\u062c\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0651\u064e\u062d\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0646\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0